.TH LPF-IMPORT 8 "June 2026" "lpf 0.1.0-dev" "lpf Manual"
.SH NAME
lpf\-import \- import existing nftables or iptables\-save policy
.SH SYNOPSIS
lpf import <nftables|iptables\-save|ufw|firewalld>
.SH DESCRIPTION
Import existing firewall state into an lpf policy starting point.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\-\-output <path>
write imported policy to a file
.SH EXAMPLES
lpf import nftables
lpf import iptables\-save < rules.v4
.SH FILES
/etc/nftables.conf
/etc/ufw
/etc/firewalld
.SH SAFETY NOTES
Untranslatable constructs must be marked explicitly and never silently dropped.
.SH EXIT STATUS
0 on success.
Non\-zero when validation, planning, or host operations fail.
.SH SEE ALSO
lpf\-check(8), lpf.conf(5)
